# static/app.html is GENERATED from the static/app/ fragments (build.rs via
# crates/app-html-assembler); edit the fragments, never the artifact.
#
# Byte-exactness pins: the artifact embeds one raw NUL byte (the
# filesIdeBufferKey separator in 55-files-ide.js), so git's heuristics have
# always treated the monolith as binary and never applied eol conversion to
# it. Make that explicit for both the artifact and the fragments (-text), so
# a Windows checkout (autocrlf=true runners) reassembles to identical bytes.
# `diff` forces text diffs for the NUL-carrying fragment, which would
# otherwise show as "Binary files differ".
static/app.html -text
static/app/** -text diff
